headline: Some Lenders Benefit From SBA’s Troubled Loan Program
summary: Changes that helped lenders hurt the U.S. Small Business Administration’s flagship lending program and many of its borrowers.  Early defaults on loans backed by the SBA are on the rise.  A Senate hearing last week studied how the SBA’s flagship loan program, known as 7(a), turned cash flow negative last year, after the agency dropped its fees and loosened its lending rules.
